holiday /ˈhɒlɪˌdeɪ/

(holidaying,holidayed,holidays) 

1. N-COUNT A holiday is a day when people do not go to work or school because of a religious or national celebration. 公众假日 

例： New Year's Day is a public holiday. 元旦是公休日。 

2.  →  see also bank holiday 

3. N-COUNT A holiday is a period of time during which you relax and enjoy yourself away from home. People sometimes refer to their holiday as their holidays . (外出度过的) 假期 [英国英语] 

例： During his summer holiday he visited Russia. 暑假期间他游览了俄罗斯。 

4. N-PLURAL The holidays are the time when children do not have to go to school. (学校的) 假期 [英国英语] 

5. N-UNCOUNT If you have a particular number of days' or weeks' holiday , you do not have to go to work for that number of days or weeks. (工作) 假期 [英国英语] 

例： The French get five to six weeks' holiday a year. 法国人一年有5到6周的假期。 

6. V-I If you are holidaying in a place away from home, you are on holiday there. (外出) 度假 [英国英语] 

例： Myles holidayed in Jamaica. 迈尔斯在牙买加度了假。

